  "answer": "**Kalpabuddha chapter 3 does not discuss or mention *bodhicitta*.**[^1]\n\nThe chapter is brief (41 words, 2 paragraphs) and describes attributes of the deity Ratnasambhava (one of the five Dhyani Buddhas in Vajrayana Buddhism): his direction (South), color (yellow), consort (Lady Māmakī), mantra (Trāṃ), *jñāna* (ākāśamata, \"equality of space\"), implement (kapāla/skull cup), and abode (inside of the spleen).[^2]\n\nA search of the full *Kalpabuddha* corpus for \"bodhicitta\" (alone or with the work title) yields no results. *Bodhicitta* (\"enlightenment mind\") appears in other Indic works like *Kunjarakarna Dharmakathana* and *San Hyan Kamahayanikan*, but not here.[^3]\n\n[^1]: *Kalpabuddha*, ch. 3 (full chapter).\n[^2]: *Kalpabuddha*, ch. 3, [p-68d96e](/works/unknown-kalpabuddha-d760dc/03/translation/#p-68d96e).\n[^3]: Corpus-wide search results for \"bodhicitta\".",
